<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - PERFORMANCE DIAGNOSTICS - Test Procedures - Boost Pressure
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Boost Pressure</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f2400649" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D3149.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Purpose</emph>
            </para>
            <para>To determine if the engine develops sufficient boost pressure at the specified RPM</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Service Tool (EST) with Master Diagnostics software</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>International&#174; EZ-Tech Interface Cable</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                        safety instructions in the foreword of this manual. Follow all warnings, cautions, and notes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Monitoring Boost Pressure using EST</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do this test at full load along with Test 15 (Fuel Pressure) and 16 (Injection Control
                        Pressure).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">See Appendix A in this manual for specifications, and record on Performance Diagnostics
                    form.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2400650" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31206.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Road Performance. ssn</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open Road Performance.ssn to monitor engine operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Monitor boost pressure or MAP.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drive vehicle and make sure engine operating temperature reaches 70&#176;C
                    (158&#176;F).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Find a long, open stretch of road.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Select a suitable gear, press accelerator pedal fully to the floor, and accelerate to
                    rated speed at 100% load.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Record EST boost pressure on diagnostics form.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If boost pressure is to spec,
                            <emph type="bold">do not continue Performance Diagnostics</emph>.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If boost pressure is not to spec, continue with Performance Diagnostic tests.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Restricted intake or exhaust</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Low fuel pressure</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Low ICP</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Control system faults</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Defective EGR valve</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Defective fuel injectors</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Defective turbocharger</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Monitoring Boost Pressure using Pressure Sensor Breakout Harness</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Pressure sensor breakout harness</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DMM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f2400651" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31147.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Pressure sensor breakout harness installed - MAP</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install pressure sensor breakout harness to MAP sensor and engine harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use DMM to measure MAP at rated speed and full load.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Connect POS to green (signal circuit) and NEG to black (ground circuit).</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>See Section 7 for operational voltages and values.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle -
                        comply with the following:
                    </para>
                    <para>When routing DMM leads, do not crimp the leads, run the leads too close to moving parts, or
                        let the leads touch hot engine surfaces. Secure the DMM and leads in the cab so as not to
                        obstruct the operator.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route DMM and leads into cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Monitor DMM voltage signal for MAP and record on Performance Diagnostics form.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drive vehicle and make sure engine operating temperature reaches 70&#176;C
                    (158&#176;F).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Find a long, open stretch of road.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Select a suitable gear, press accelerator pedal fully to the floor, and accelerate to
                    rated speed at 100% load.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Record DMM voltage reading on diagnostics form.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If boost pressure is to spec,
                            <emph type="bold">do not continue Performance Diagnostics</emph>.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If boost pressure is not to spec, continue with Performance Diagnostic tests.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
